The evidence with the title 'Why are food prices so high? ' says Mar 15, 2012  ... Food prices have skyrocketed over the past couple years . While overall U.S. food prices rose about 5 % last year, earlier in the year food inflation was the highest recorded in 36 years . The USDA sees food prices rising 2.5%-3.5% in 2012 but many believe that inflation could be much higher . [  ... ] 
